45-41 Aest 127th Street, north side, between Lenox and Fifth Avenues. Nos. 45-43 are now four-story frame houses with brick fronts. They were formerly three-stories with basements.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection,Wuseum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 607.

715479f-a.text:
48-54 West 127th Street, south side, east of Lenox avenue. No. 50 is a three-story and No. 48 is a two-story frame house.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 46

49-47 West 127th Street, north side, east of Lenox Avenue. Both of these are four-story frame houses, No. 49 with a combination brick and stucco front and No. 47 all brick front. Both these houses
were formerly three-stories.
1932.
J. Clarence Davies Collection, Museum of the City of New York.
Negative No. 602.
